@page "/header-footer"
<PageTitle>Header &amp; Footer - Saascade Docs</PageTitle>

<h1 id="header-footer">Header &amp; Footer</h1>

<div class="doc-layout">

<main class="documentation">

    <TechCard>
        <section class="card">

            <h2 id="header">Header</h2>

            <p class="subtitle">
                The Header component renders a semantic header element for introductory content
                or navigation.
            </p>

            <hr />

            <pre><code>&lt;Header&gt;
    &lt;H1&gt;Welcome&lt;/H1&gt;
    &lt;Navbar&gt;...&lt;/Navbar&gt;
&lt;/Header&gt;</code></pre>

        </section>
    </TechCard>

    <TechCard>
        <section class="card">

            <h2 id="footer">Footer</h2>

            <p class="subtitle">
                The Footer component renders a semantic footer element for page or section footers.
            </p>

            <pre><code>&lt;Footer&gt;
    &lt;P&gt;&amp;copy; 2025 Saascade&lt;/P&gt;
&lt;/Footer&gt;</code></pre>

        </section>
    </TechCard>

    <TechCard Tech="bootstrap">
        <section class="card">

            <h2 id="header-footer-bootstrap">Bootstrap 5 Header &amp; Footer</h2>

            <p class="subtitle">Bootstrap 5 Header &amp; Footer</p>

            <hr />

            <p>
                In Bootstrap 5, the Header and Footer components render as their standard HTML
                semantic elements. Bootstrap uses the Navbar component class for navigation
                bars placed inside the header. The Footer element typically receives Bootstrap
                utility classes such as bg-dark or text-light through the Class parameter to
                establish the footer's visual appearance.
            </p>

        </section>
    </TechCard>

    <TechCard Tech="daisyui">
        <section class="card">

            <h2 id="header-footer-daisyui">DaisyUI Header &amp; Footer</h2>

            <p class="subtitle">DaisyUI Header &amp; Footer</p>

            <hr />

            <p>
                In DaisyUI, the Header component wraps DaisyUI's navbar component and any other
                introductory content. The Footer component maps to DaisyUI's footer class, which
                provides a structured footer layout with support for footer-title sections and
                multi-column link groups. DaisyUI's footer is theme-aware and adapts its
                background and text colors to the active theme.
            </p>

        </section>
    </TechCard>

    <TechCard Tech="basecoat">
        <section class="card">

            <h2 id="header-footer-basecoat">Basecoat Header &amp; Footer</h2>

            <p class="subtitle">Basecoat Header &amp; Footer</p>

            <hr />

            <p>
                In Basecoat, the Header and Footer components are styled with Tailwind utility
                classes. The Header typically receives flex layout and padding utilities to
                position the logo, navigation, and action buttons. The Footer receives
                background and text color utilities along with a grid layout for multi-column
                link sections. All styling is controlled through Tailwind utilities passed
                via Class or Specialization.
            </p>

        </section>
    </TechCard>

</main>

<TableOfContents Items="@([
    new TocItem("header-footer", "Header & Footer"),
    new TocItem("header", "Header", 2),
    new TocItem("footer", "Footer", 2),
    new TocItem("header-footer-bootstrap", "Bootstrap 5", 2),
    new TocItem("header-footer-daisyui", "DaisyUI", 2),
    new TocItem("header-footer-basecoat", "Basecoat", 2)
])" />

</div>
